tely<br />gone away, because now you not only need to do the putname() in the<br />caller, you need to do it _conditionally_.<br /><br />So please don't do this.<br /><br />The other patches also all make it *really* hard to follow when<br />putname() is done - because depending on the context, you have to do<br />it when returning an error, or when an error was not returned.<br /><br />I really think this is a huge mistake. Don't do it this way. NAK NAK NAK.<br /><br />Please instead of making this all completely messy and completely<br />impossible to follow the rule about exactly who does "putname()" and<br />under what conditions, just leave the slight duplication in place.<br /><br />Duplicating simple helper routines is *good*. Complex and<br />hard-to-understand and non-intuitive rules are *bad*.<br /><br />You're adding badness.<br /><br />                 Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
